maps.name: Grouped Concept
maps.description:
# Overview
This causal loop diagram (CLD) aims to help stakeholders understand the complex link between loneliness, social isolation, and chronic diseases. This is part of a National Health and Medical Research Council (NHMRC)-funded Targeted Call for Research (TCR) into loneliness, social isolation and chronic disease management. This preliminary version of the diagram is based on an initial Group Model Building (GMB) workshop involving policymakers, researchers, and community members conducted in April 2024. Stakeholders identified over 100 concepts relating to loneliness, social isolation and chronic disease through small and large group exercises. The list of "concepts" was then condensed and grouped by the Connecting for Better Health (C4BH) project core modelling team at Monash University, Australia. We aim to conduct a second GMB workshop in December 2024 to finalise the diagram.
